tever . . . may be necessary” and “fully” are omitted as surplus. The words “with the Secretary” are substituted for “in any monitoring of their programs” for clarity.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcc77a14f-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcc77a150-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Enactment of the Pipeline Safety Improvement Act of 2002, referred to in subsec. (b)(3), is the enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/355"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–355","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-12-17"},"text":"Dec. 17, 2002","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcc77a151-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2016—Subsec. (b)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/183/s24/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–183, § 24(b)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/183/s13"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–183, § 13","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/355/s4/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–355, § 4(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Agreements Without Certification","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"General Authority","children":[],"tail":"” in heading."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/355/s4/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–355, § 4(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (b). Former subsec. (b) redesignated (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/355/s4/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–355, § 4(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (c), redesignated subsec. (b) as (c), designated existing provisions as par. (1), inserted par. heading, realigned margins, and added par. (2). Former subsec. (c) redesignated (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/355/s4/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–355, § 4(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (c) as (d). Former subsec. (d) redesignated (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/355/s4/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–355, § 4(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (b), redesignated subsec. (d) as (e), reenacted heading without change and amended text generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Secretary may end an agreement made under this section when the Secretary finds that the State authority has not complied with any provision of the agreement. The Secretary shall give the authority notice and an opportunity for a hearing before ending an agreement. The finding and decision to end the agreement shall be published in the Federal Register and may not become effective for at least 15 days after the date of publication.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/304"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–304","children":[],"tail":" substituted “State pipeline safety agreements” for “State agreements” in section catchline."}]